^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 308 - August 5, 2002^*N
^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
It is always nice to see your friends do well in a major event, especially when they were not among the pre-tournament favorites. In this year's Spingold (which was played at the recent ACBL Summer NABC in Washington DC), the unheralded ^*BMoss^*N team advanced all the way to the Finals before losing to the ^*BJacobs^*N Team.

Team Moss consisted of 2 of my close friends and former teammates, ^*BAllan Graves^*N and ^*BBryan Maksymetz^*N along with ^*BMike Moss^*N (who happens to be the father of my regular partner ^*BBrad Moss^*N) and ^*BMartin Shifko^*N, a brilliant young player from Austria. That's right - there were only 4 players on the Moss team (up to 6 players are allowed) which makes their accomplishment all the more remarkable.

I am also friendly with the players on the Jacobs Team (^*BGeorge Jacobs^*N-^*BRalph Katz^*N, ^*BLorenzo Lauria^*N-^*BAlfredo Versace^*N, and ^*BNorberto Bocchi^*B-^*BGiorgio Duboin^*N), but these guys have done so much winning during the last few years that it was very hard not to root for the underdog Moss team. Still, our congratulations go out to the Jacobs Team. Both Allan Graves and Bryan Maksymetz told me by e-mail that the Jacobs Team played great bridge (especially in the 4th quarter) and that they thoroughly deserved to win the 2002 Spingold.

This week's deal features Allan as declarer in a very ambitious slam from the first quarter of the Spingold Final.
