nt|Allan Graves has been one of Canada's very best players for over 20 years and he has come close to winning several World Championships over the years. I have spent a lot of time talking bridge with Allan since shortly after I learned the game in the 1980s. His bridge wisdom is considerable and I have learned a great deal from my discussions with Allan and from my experiences playing on teams with him.

Besides being a great player, Allan is also an extraordinary bridge teacher. He is able to work with players of all levels of ability and his patient and friendly disposition ensure that his students are always in a good frame of mind for learning.

We are very fortunate that Allan has been doing a lot of online teaching through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N (both to individual students and to groups). While ^*BBridge Base Online^*N is an entirely free service, Allan makes his living from teaching bridge and it is necessary for him to receive payment when he teaches online. You can find out more about the services that Allan has to offer by sending him e-mail:

